24class BasicBlockProfilerData {
25 public:
26 explicit BasicBlockProfilerData(size_t n_blocks);
27 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE BasicBlockProfilerData(
28 Handle<OnHeapBasicBlockProfilerData> js_heap_data, Isolate* isolate);
29 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE BasicBlockProfilerData(
30 Tagged<OnHeapBasicBlockProfilerData> js_heap_data);
31
32 BasicBlockProfilerData(const BasicBlockProfilerData&) = delete;
33 BasicBlockProfilerData& operator=(const BasicBlockProfilerData&) = delete;
34
35 size_t n_blocks() const {
36 DCHECK_EQ(block_ids_.size(), counts_.size());
37 return block_ids_.size();
38 }
39 const uint32_t* counts() const { return &counts_[0]; }
40
41 void SetCode(const std::ostringstream& os);
42 void SetFunctionName(std::unique_ptr<char[]> name);
43 void SetSchedule(const std::ostringstream& os);
44 void SetBlockId(size_t offset, int32_t id);
45 void SetHash(int hash);
46 void AddBranch(int32_t true_block_id, int32_t false_block_id);
47
48 // Copy the data from this object into an equivalent object stored on the JS
49 // heap, so that it can survive snapshotting and relocation. This must
50 // happen on the main thread during finalization of the compilation.
51 Handle<OnHeapBasicBlockProfilerData> CopyToJSHeap(Isolate* isolate);
52
53 void Log(Isolate* isolate, std::ostream& os);
54
55 private:
56 friend class BasicBlockProfiler;
57 friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os,
58 const BasicBlockProfilerData& s);
59
60 V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE void ResetCounts();
61
62 void CopyFromJSHeap(Tagged<OnHeapBasicBlockProfilerData> js_heap_data);
63
64 // These vectors are indexed by reverse post-order block number.
65 std::vector<int32_t> block_ids_;
66 std::vector<uint32_t> counts_;
67 std::vector<std::pair<int32_t, int32_t>> branches_;
68 std::string function_name_;
69 std::string schedule_;
70 std::string code_;
71 int hash_ = 0;
72};

104// This struct comprises all callee inside a block.
105using BlockCallees = std::set<Builtin>;
106// This struct describes a call inside a caller, the key is block id, the value
107// is a set of callee builtins.
108using BuiltinCallees = std::unordered_map<int32_t, BlockCallees>;
109// This struct describes a map for all builtins which will call other builtin.
110using BuiltinCallMap = std::unordered_map<Builtin, BuiltinCallees>;
111
112class BuiltinsCallGraph {
113 public:
114 BuiltinsCallGraph();
115 ~BuiltinsCallGraph() = default;
116 BuiltinsCallGraph(const BuiltinsCallGraph&) = delete;
117 BuiltinsCallGraph& operator=(const BuiltinsCallGraph&) = delete;
118
119 static BuiltinsCallGraph* Get();
120 void AddBuiltinCall(Builtin caller, Builtin callee, int32_t block_id);
121 const BuiltinCallees* GetBuiltinCallees(Builtin builtin);
122 V8_INLINE bool all_hash_matched() const { return all_hash_matched_; }
123 V8_INLINE void set_all_hash_matched(bool all_hash_matched) {
124 all_hash_matched_ = all_hash_matched;
125 }
126
127 private:
128 BuiltinCallMap builtin_call_map_;
129 bool all_hash_matched_;
130};
